column5: Anyone have any dealings with them? If so you might want to get more info ASAP. A friend just got contacted on facebook by a friend of his who posted a picture of a notice on their window, apparently it went down yesterday at 5pm. If they lock down everything it could be bad news for anyone who has a boat there.

That would suck..This happened to my sister..Was having final alterations done to her wedding dress a month before the wedding and the shop was locked down with her dress in it.. Oh what an ordeal that was..Yikes...
I wonder if it applies to all six of their locations?
Probably posted on the door with the reflection off the glass would cause that.
http://www.farberfinancial.com/insolvency-engagements/crate-marine-sales-limited-et-al  Still too knew for even the receiver to share details.
Even the mechanics tools will be locked in.Looks like several numbered companies listed on the sheet. Likely all their locations.
I found this the other day.  http://www.quintenews.com/2014/11/crates-marine-belleville-not-affected-ryan-crate/76145/
